						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in Survey No. 66.</p>						

						<p>Circa 15th century.</p>						

						<p>It states that the village of Kṛishṇarāyasamudra was granted as an <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> to the <hi rend="italic">Brāhmaṇas</hi> and it was indicated by the stone with the figure of Vāmana bearing the epigraph. The record was engraved by Kariyōja son of Dēvōja.</p>						

